quote:
'Let me live in my house by the side of the road,Where the race of men go by; 
They are good, they are bad; they are weak, they are strong. Wise, foolish.; 
—so am I Then why should I sit in the scorner's seat, Or hurl the cynic's ban? 
Let me live in my house by the side of the road, And be a friend to man.' - Sam Walter Foss
